WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.580
<i>Previously on Will Trent…</i>

2
00:00:02.660 --> 00:00:04.670
You have no sightings
of Adelaide Trevens?

3
00:00:05.830 --> 00:00:07.920
Goodbye. Will Trent.

4
00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:11.470
If you know where Antonio Morales is.
you need to tell me.

5
00:00:13.340 --> 00:00:14.840
We'll be in touch.

6
00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:18.220
Oh. You think I'm holding
out on you. huh?

7
00:00:18.310 --> 00:00:22.430
Caroline. is there any new intel
on Adelaide Trevens

8
00:00:22.520 --> 00:00:24.350
that we have not forwarded
to Special Agent Trent?

9
00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:27.150
No. ma'am. You gave me
clear instructions to share everything.

10
00:00:27.230 --> 00:00:31.610
I look at you and the career you've had
and what it's cost.

11
00:00:31.690 --> 00:00:33.780
I don't know if I can do this job anymore.

12
00:00:34.360 --> 00:00:36.240
If you tell anyone
about this call.

13
00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:39.240
I'll remove your uncle's organs
with a rusty spoon and a smile.

14
00:00:39.830 --> 00:00:42.750
So be a good boy. Special Agent Trent.

15
00:00:42.830 --> 00:00:43.910
I'll be waiting.

16
00:00:47.330 --> 00:00:53.630
If you had to choose. would you
rather live on a star or in space?

17
00:00:55.510 --> 00:00:57.840
What? Like. alone?

18
00:00:59.720 --> 00:01:00.810
No. you can have friends.

19
00:01:00.890 --> 00:01:03.600
I hate being hot. Space.

20
00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:05.440
Me too.

21
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.150
Is your edible hitting?

22
00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:11.940
- Uh. I can't tell.
- Hmm.

23
00:01:16.450 --> 00:01:17.450
Hide the gummies.

24
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:25.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

25
00:01:28.960 --> 00:01:32.380
Whoa! Oh!

26
00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:35.590
Who the hell is that?

27
00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:40.800
The gummy is definitely hitting.

28
00:01:47.020 --> 00:01:49.400
It's just that I'm trying to anticipate
her next move.

29
00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:51.610
and I'm having trouble
getting inside her head.

30
00:01:51.690 --> 00:01:54.360
Yes. but I can't analyze
somebody I've never met.

31
00:01:54.440 --> 00:01:55.570
I'm your therapist.

32
00:01:55.650 --> 00:01:56.950
Come on. Dr. Roach.

33
00:01:57.530 --> 00:01:59.870
Look. I trust your opinion. Please.

34
00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:01.530
Flattery? Really?

35
00:02:02.370 --> 00:02:03.370
All right.

36
00:02:04.410 --> 00:02:06.620
- You're overthinking it.
- What do you mean?

37
00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:08.210
Will. from what you've told me.

38
00:02:08.290 --> 00:02:11.590
Adelaide's pathology
is dominated by two factors:

39
00:02:12.210 --> 00:02:15.380
genetic predisposition
to antisocial behavior

40
00:02:15.880 --> 00:02:17.800
and overwhelming childhood trauma.

41
00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.390
Okay. what about her family history?

42
00:02:20.470 --> 00:02:24.350
The rejection of her father. her need
to control people the way he did?

43
00:02:24.850 --> 00:02:28.060
So you want to use those details
to construct a train of logic

44
00:02:28.140 --> 00:02:29.440
that you can hop on board

45
00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:32.940
and... choo choo! ride all the way
to finding your uncle Antonio.

46
00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:36.190
Great. We're back to analyzing me again.

47
00:02:36.280 --> 00:02:39.110
Well. that's because you have a brain
that can be analyzed.

48
00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:41.160
Your behavior contains logic.

49
00:02:41.240 --> 00:02:46.330
That's not all.
You feel desire. empathy. guilt.

50
00:02:47.330 --> 00:02:50.080
Will Trent. you are a deep.
deep well of humanity.

51
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:54.250
- You're saying Adelaide is different?
- Very different.

52
00:02:55.800 --> 00:03:01.300
A psychology as damaged as hers.
it's unpredictable. chaotic.

53
00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:03.100
You're an amazing detective.

54
00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:06.430
but even you will not be able
to piece together exactly

55
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:09.560
what she wants from you.
because I don't think she knows either.

56
00:03:09.640 --> 00:03:11.850
I mean. think about
when you first met her.

57
00:03:11.940 --> 00:03:16.020
She was pretending to be law enforcement.
You're a special agent.

58
00:03:16.110 --> 00:03:19.190
She was trying on the experience
of being you.

59
00:03:19.990 --> 00:03:22.910
Then came the flirting.
I don't know if you want to dig into that.

60
00:03:22.990 --> 00:03:24.660
No. I do not.

61
00:03:24.740 --> 00:03:28.120
Then she forced you to relive
the circumstances of your mother's death.

62
00:03:28.830 --> 00:03:30.500
I'm very sorry that she did that.
by the way.

63
00:03:31.870 --> 00:03:34.210
Yeah. Me too.

64
00:03:34.290 --> 00:03:36.420
Then she tried to kill you.
A few times. you said.

65
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:38.800
No. just twice.

66
00:03:38.880 --> 00:03:41.510
So you're saying she's crazy. right?

67
00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:44.090
Will. you know.
I don't really like to use that word.

68
00:03:44.180 --> 00:03:48.810
So at any point. she might be trying
to be me. screw me. trick me or kill me.

69
00:03:48.890 --> 00:03:50.100
I mean. that's pretty crazy.

70
00:03:50.730 --> 00:03:53.150
And you won't know which.

71
00:04:00.280 --> 00:04:04.030
Oh. what about this?
"Real estate operations and financing"?

72
00:04:04.110 --> 00:04:07.120
No. no. no. no. no. You're not going
to be a real estate agent.

73
00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:09.120
Why not? I watch enough HGTV.

74
00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:11.330
Because real estate agents need
to be chipper.

75
00:04:11.410 --> 00:04:13.370
and you dole out smiles
like they cost you money.

76
00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:16.840
Yeah. well. maybe I would smile more if
I wasn't confronted with death every day.

77
00:04:16.920 --> 00:04:20.130
I joined the APD because my mom was a cop.

78
00:04:20.210 --> 00:04:22.880
and then I was pushed into GBI
because of my aunt Mandy.

79
00:04:22.970 --> 00:04:26.430
I just feel like sometimes
my life happened

80
00:04:26.510 --> 00:04:29.060
without me making
any decisions along the way.

81
00:04:29.560 --> 00:04:31.270
I want to take control of my future.

82
00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:34.310
You know how many people depend
on the GBI? Your job's important.

83
00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:36.810
Yeah. a lot of jobs are important.
People need houses.

84
00:04:36.900 --> 00:04:40.230
Interesting. fun.
and every day is different.

85
00:04:40.320 --> 00:04:43.280
I could get killed on the job at any time.

86
00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:46.530
I want to grow old enough
to see my kid win a Grammy one day.

87
00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:48.070
You know what? Fine.

88
00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:51.240
Leave the GBI. follow your bliss.
and go to bed every night

89
00:04:51.330 --> 00:04:53.290
and try not to think about all the people
who won't get justice

90
00:04:53.370 --> 00:04:56.120
- because you're not on the job.
- What do you care. as long as I pay rent?

91
00:04:56.210 --> 00:04:58.460
Oh.

92
00:04:59.710 --> 00:05:01.340
Mmm. I gotta get this. Sorry.

93
00:05:02.090 --> 00:05:03.340
What's up. Austin?

94
00:05:05.340 --> 00:05:08.510
Is everyone okay?
Yeah. yeah. I'll be right there.

95
00:05:09.220 --> 00:05:11.970
Old army buddy.
His teenager just got carjacked.

96
00:05:12.850 --> 00:05:15.390
I told him I would help him. but…

97
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:18.150
Max has your car for the night.

98
00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:21.230
- Right.
- And you need to borrow mine.

99
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:25.450
- For justice and honor…
- Mm-hmm.

100
00:05:25.530 --> 00:05:27.110
…and the order of society.

101
00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:30.280
And I'll get you a burrito
from Jimmy's Bean Shack on the way back.

102
00:05:32.450 --> 00:05:33.540
Okay.

103
00:05:42.250 --> 00:05:44.800
- You said you got carjacked.
- We did.

104
00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:46.680
Austin. truck's right there.

105
00:05:46.760 --> 00:05:48.050
Yeah. but she locked herself inside.

106
00:05:48.130 --> 00:05:50.140
and these two dumbasses
left the keys in the ignition.

107
00:05:50.220 --> 00:05:51.390
That's car-squatting.

108
00:05:51.970 --> 00:05:53.890
- What happened?
- She didn't say anything.

109
00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:56.180
She just jumped in the truck
and locked the doors.

110
00:05:56.270 --> 00:06:00.150
- And you don't know her?
- I think she's a junkie. She is not right.

111
00:06:00.230 --> 00:06:02.270
She hasn't said a word this entire time.

112
00:06:02.360 --> 00:06:05.150
Hold on. She doesn't look high to me.
Let me try.

113
00:06:16.540 --> 00:06:17.750
Hi.

114
00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:22.250
Are you hungry? I have granola bars.

115
00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:26.340
Do you like berry or peanut butter?

116
00:06:34.310 --> 00:06:38.230
My name is Faith. I'm here to help you.

117
00:06:39.980 --> 00:06:41.230
Can you tell me what you need?

118
00:06:43.610 --> 00:06:46.360
Okay. Can you tell me your name?

119
00:06:51.490 --> 00:06:53.070
You're not in any trouble.

120
00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:55.240
I just want to make sure that you're okay.

121
00:06:56.330 --> 00:06:57.660
Are you still hungry?

122
00:06:59.710 --> 00:07:02.710
How about you open the door.
and I can give you the other bar?

123
00:07:20.520 --> 00:07:22.850
You don't have any shoes on.
How'd you get here?

124
00:07:28.070 --> 00:07:29.360
Aliens.

125
00:07:30.070 --> 00:07:32.610
- What was that?
- The aliens took me.

126
00:07:56.180 --> 00:07:57.260
Well?

127
00:07:59.350 --> 00:08:02.230
A woman matching
Adelaide Trevens's physical profile

128
00:08:02.310 --> 00:08:05.940
was spotted crossing the Anzalduas
Port of Entry into Texas.

129
00:08:06.020 --> 00:08:07.360
Does the FBI know where she is now?

130
00:08:07.940 --> 00:08:09.610
- We're working on it.
- Was she alone?

131
00:08:09.690 --> 00:08:12.070
Is there any reason to believe
that Antonio Morales is with her?

132
00:08:12.150 --> 00:08:13.780
We don't know that yet.

133
00:08:14.990 --> 00:08:16.320
Has your Agent Trent heard from her?

134
00:08:16.410 --> 00:08:18.830
No. I would have told you if he had.

135
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:21.910
Are you sure he would tell you?

136
00:08:23.620 --> 00:08:25.790
I'd be a lot more confident in your answer

137
00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:28.130
if he would simply let us monitor
that phone.

138
00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:30.090
He doesn't trust the FBI.

139
00:08:30.170 --> 00:08:32.170
He knows you're more interested
in apprehending Adelaide

140
00:08:32.260 --> 00:08:33.260
than finding his uncle.

141
00:08:33.340 --> 00:08:34.590
She killed one of ours.

142
00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:37.260
Oh. is that the reason
for these spy games?

143
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:40.560
You know. I had to pull in
a decade-old IOU to get you to talk to me.

144
00:08:40.640 --> 00:08:42.430
and even then it's like this.

145
00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:45.270
I feel like I'm buying drugs.

146
00:08:46.190 --> 00:08:47.900
Do you guys have any actionable leads?

147
00:08:49.020 --> 00:08:50.440
We made progress on one thing.

148
00:08:51.940 --> 00:08:53.820
We compiled a list of persons of interest

149
00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:55.610
for the young man
who gave Agent Trent the phone.

150
00:08:56.910 --> 00:08:58.530
- The Commander?
- Yeah.

151
00:08:58.620 --> 00:09:00.990
It's a long list. but we're working on
whittling it down.

152
00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:02.750
In the meantime…

153
00:09:04.620 --> 00:09:05.620
I know.

154
00:09:07.330 --> 00:09:08.840
This stays between us.

155
00:09:19.510 --> 00:09:20.890
- Hey.
- Hey.

156
00:09:20.970 --> 00:09:23.680
Still no ID. If she's from the area.
no one's looking for her.

157
00:09:23.770 --> 00:09:26.190
I asked Angie
to expand the search nationwide.

158
00:09:26.270 --> 00:09:27.770
Was she sexually assaulted?

159
00:09:28.350 --> 00:09:30.770
Don't know.
She won't let doctors examine her.

160
00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.740
- Hi. How is she?
- Hi.

161
00:09:34.820 --> 00:09:38.360
She says she can't remember her name
or anything that happened to her.

162
00:09:38.450 --> 00:09:40.410
She says that the aliens wiped her memory.

163
00:09:40.490 --> 00:09:42.160
You think she's lying to protect someone?

164
00:09:42.240 --> 00:09:44.450
She looks shook up to me. Maybe PTSD?

165
00:09:44.540 --> 00:09:45.790
It could be.

166
00:09:45.870 --> 00:09:48.830
What is she doing? Drawing?

167
00:09:48.920 --> 00:09:50.750
Oh. I left her a notepad.

168
00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:54.510
You know. sometimes when a patient
won't talk. they'll write or draw instead.

169
00:09:55.010 --> 00:09:56.510
- It's actually a really good sign.
- Mmm.

170
00:09:56.590 --> 00:09:58.970
- If you'll excuse me. I'll be back.
- Thank you.

171
00:10:00.970 --> 00:10:02.720
You know you don't have
to assist on this. right?

172
00:10:02.810 --> 00:10:03.850
Yeah. it's okay.

173
00:10:03.930 --> 00:10:06.980
Will's out with a bug that's been going
around. and I'm between cases.

174
00:10:07.060 --> 00:10:09.190
No. I mean. seeing as you have
one foot out the door.

175
00:10:11.230 --> 00:10:14.360
Remember that time you told me
you hadn't pooped in six days?

176
00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:17.360
How is that relevant?

177
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:20.120
Did I bring it up every five minutes
while you were trying to work?

178
00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:22.330
No. You told me to eat more fiber.

179
00:10:22.410 --> 00:10:25.580
That's right.
There's a lesson in there. You'll find it.

180
00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:28.000
- I told you that in confidence.
- Mmm.

181
00:10:34.460 --> 00:10:38.840
Hi. I brought you some pants.
Hospital gowns are the worst.

182
00:10:40.510 --> 00:10:44.390
Do you want to hear a story
about my dog when I was a kid?

183
00:10:47.020 --> 00:10:51.650
Okay. so my mom brought him home
from work one day.

184
00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:56.030
He had three legs and one eye.
His name was Gremlin.

185
00:10:56.110 --> 00:10:58.610
He had a lot of mortal enemies.

186
00:10:58.700 --> 00:11:03.370
including the vacuum cleaner.
the mailman. any set of stairs and rain.

187
00:11:04.240 --> 00:11:05.620
but he loved me.

188
00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:09.620
He would sleep right here.

189
00:11:10.830 --> 00:11:11.830
Every night.

190
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:16.460
He kept me warm and safe.

191
00:11:18.380 --> 00:11:20.340
You want to see what he looked like?

192
00:11:29.100 --> 00:11:30.480
Do you like to draw?

193
00:11:32.850 --> 00:11:33.860
Hmm?

194
00:11:34.610 --> 00:11:36.070
Can I see?

195
00:11:47.120 --> 00:11:48.120
Thank you.

196
00:11:52.120 --> 00:11:53.830
That's the one that watched me.

197
00:11:58.920 --> 00:11:59.920
It's a sign.

198
00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:02.930
A sign?
That we should call Mulder and Scully?

199
00:12:03.010 --> 00:12:04.970
No. dummy. it's a literal sign.

200
00:12:05.050 --> 00:12:08.010
Shelly's Alien Emporium
off the freeway in Grove Park. Come on.

201
00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:24.200
Oh. you're right.
That's the alien.

202
00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:26.570
Maybe this is where she was taken from.

203
00:12:26.660 --> 00:12:27.700
This place looks incredible.

204
00:12:27.780 --> 00:12:29.620
Look at all the satellite dishes
on the roof.

205
00:12:29.700 --> 00:12:31.450
What does Shelly know that we don't?

206
00:12:31.540 --> 00:12:33.460
Hopefully something about our Jane Doe.

207
00:12:40.460 --> 00:12:43.010
- Oh. This place is...
- A lot.

208
00:12:43.760 --> 00:12:45.130
I was gonna say "amazing."

209
00:12:53.100 --> 00:12:58.650
Welcome to Shelly's Alien Emporium.

210
00:12:58.730 --> 00:13:01.400
Georgia's oldest
and most comprehensive library

211
00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:04.240
of extraterrestrial documentation.

212
00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:05.450
I'm Shelly.

213
00:13:05.530 --> 00:13:08.620
Hi. Shelly.
We. uh. have a few questions for you.

214
00:13:09.200 --> 00:13:10.580
Well. it's about time.

215
00:13:11.240 --> 00:13:17.880
February 8. 1972. I was taken
from a Montgomery Ward parking lot.

216
00:13:17.960 --> 00:13:20.170
They kept me for nine days.
ran their tests.

217
00:13:20.250 --> 00:13:22.880
and put me back down behind
the Clermont Lounge

218
00:13:22.960 --> 00:13:25.800
in completely different clothes.

219
00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:30.720
It's all here in my book. Alienated.

220
00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:32.970
We're actually here
to talk about a missing girl.

221
00:13:33.060 --> 00:13:35.350
Yeah. she said she was abducted too.

222
00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:38.440
Greens or grays? Any missing time?
Where'd they take her from?

223
00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:42.070
Maybe around here.
She actually drew a picture of your sign.

224
00:13:42.150 --> 00:13:45.530
Here? No. No way.
I-I would have picked it up.

225
00:13:45.610 --> 00:13:47.820
- With your satellite dishes?
- Uh-huh. That's right.

226
00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:52.540
I'll be the first to know when another
ship hits the greater southeast airspace.

227
00:13:52.620 --> 00:13:54.290
Do you have any video cameras
up there. Shelly?

228
00:13:54.370 --> 00:13:58.790
No. no. no. By the time they're close
enough for video. well. you'll know it.

229
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:01.380
You'll taste them first.
Licorice.

230
00:14:01.460 --> 00:14:04.340
Mm-hmm. That's how you know they're close.

231
00:14:04.420 --> 00:14:06.630
You won't hear the ship. It's silent.

232
00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:10.970
But you'll feel a humming
in your squishy bits.

233
00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:12.060
Okay.

234
00:14:12.140 --> 00:14:14.430
Our Jane Doe didn't mention that.

235
00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:16.140
Have you ever seen this girl before?

236
00:14:17.230 --> 00:14:19.400
Oh. her? Yeah. I've seen her.

237
00:14:19.480 --> 00:14:23.360
Down the street. coming out
of that hotel diner with her grandma.

238
00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:25.280
Her grandma?

239
00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:27.570
Yeah. or seemed like her grandma.

240
00:14:27.650 --> 00:14:32.950
Sometimes aliens shape-shift.
so you never can be sure.

241
00:14:33.030 --> 00:14:35.700
Maybe a week ago.

242
00:14:35.790 --> 00:14:40.920
I remember.
'cause she was staring at me all

243
00:14:41.830 --> 00:14:43.380
haunted-like.

244
00:14:51.260 --> 00:14:52.260
This is her room.

245
00:14:52.930 --> 00:14:54.510
The vines are the curtains.

246
00:14:56.310 --> 00:14:59.940
Okay. Hey. we're gonna need the
registration information for this room.

247
00:15:00.020 --> 00:15:01.190
Yeah. I'll get it for you.

248
00:15:01.900 --> 00:15:04.440
Okay. luggage is gone.
Room has been cleaned.

249
00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:06.480
Looks like they checked out.
but where's Grandma?

250
00:15:08.900 --> 00:15:12.780
Hey. Polaski. can you send a crime scene
unit to the Sleep Away Inn in Grove Park?

251
00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:14.620
Yeah. thanks.

252
00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:18.540
Hey. Faith. Look at this.

253
00:15:24.540 --> 00:15:25.920
No shower curtain.

254
00:15:33.340 --> 00:15:34.470
We found Grandma.

255
00:16:03.500 --> 00:16:04.500
Adelaide.

256
00:16:04.580 --> 00:16:06.920
Oh. I do love how you say my name.

257
00:16:08.050 --> 00:16:12.050
There's always a little something
in the way you say it.

258
00:16:12.130 --> 00:16:14.590
- Contempt?
- You can only hate the things you love.

259
00:16:17.930 --> 00:16:20.390
Guess what I'm holding right now.

260
00:16:22.560 --> 00:16:25.150
Oh. my God. Don't worry.

261
00:16:25.230 --> 00:16:27.690
What did you think?
It was Antonio's head?

262
00:16:28.940 --> 00:16:30.280
It's a matchbox.

263
00:16:31.570 --> 00:16:33.950
From Rio's. Remember?

264
00:16:34.030 --> 00:16:36.450
Yeah. The bar in Puerto Rico.

265
00:16:36.530 --> 00:16:37.740
I carry it with me.

266
00:16:39.870 --> 00:16:40.950
I like to touch it.

267
00:16:43.830 --> 00:16:46.630
I saw you watching me dance
that night. Will.

268
00:16:47.920 --> 00:16:54.180
Wishing you could take me.
move me however you chose.

269
00:16:54.930 --> 00:16:57.180
- Tell me I'm wrong.
- No.

270
00:16:58.550 --> 00:16:59.720
You're not wrong.

271
00:17:02.770 --> 00:17:03.940
I wanna see you.

272
00:17:05.690 --> 00:17:06.770
Tomorrow?

273
00:17:07.520 --> 00:17:08.900
I'd like that very much.

274
00:17:10.860 --> 00:17:12.610
How do you feel about small plates?

275
00:17:13.280 --> 00:17:16.570
I don't usually like to share.
but I would with you.

276
00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:18.660
Well. I don't want
to share you with anyone.

277
00:17:20.700 --> 00:17:23.830
What about my uncle? I need proof of life.

278
00:17:23.910 --> 00:17:25.460
We'll discuss over dinner.

279
00:17:26.790 --> 00:17:28.500
Le Bon Nosh. 8:00 p.m.

280
00:17:29.250 --> 00:17:33.300
Come alone. and for God's sake.
don't tell anyone.

281
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:36.090
That'll just piss me off.

282
00:17:36.720 --> 00:17:39.470
Of course. It'll be good to see you.

283
00:17:40.050 --> 00:17:41.060
And. uh…

284
00:17:43.060 --> 00:17:44.390
Adelaide…

285
00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:45.520
Yes?

286
00:17:48.020 --> 00:17:52.320
Don't shower.
I liked how you smelled in the jungle.

287
00:17:55.070 --> 00:17:56.320
Goodbye. Will.

288
00:18:00.450 --> 00:18:04.790
So our grandma is Denise Hensley.
55 years old.

289
00:18:04.870 --> 00:18:07.580
Oh. record goes back decades.
mostly solicitation and pandering.

290
00:18:07.670 --> 00:18:09.880
I'm sorry. When did you take my office?

291
00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:12.420
I am on desk duty.
and you are in the field.

292
00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:14.800
So it only makes sense.
I requisitioned it.

293
00:18:14.880 --> 00:18:18.050
Hey. guys.
I got Pete's autopsy report.

294
00:18:18.130 --> 00:18:19.800
Cause of death was blunt-force trauma.

295
00:18:19.890 --> 00:18:21.760
One of the blows
severed her vertebral artery.

296
00:18:21.850 --> 00:18:22.890
It could have been intentional.

297
00:18:22.970 --> 00:18:25.020
So the two of them
were together.

298
00:18:25.100 --> 00:18:28.350
bad guys came in. beat up Denise Hensley.
and the girl escaped.

299
00:18:28.440 --> 00:18:32.270
Not quite. Time of death
was approximately 16 hours ago.

300
00:18:32.360 --> 00:18:34.280
She was killed after our Jane Doe escaped?

301
00:18:34.360 --> 00:18:36.400
- Or maybe because she escaped?
- Yes.

302
00:18:36.490 --> 00:18:40.780
And she's not the girl's grandma
or mother or aunt.

303
00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:43.620
Not by blood. anyway.
No shared DNA.

304
00:18:46.120 --> 00:18:48.120
Can I get a peanut M&M?

305
00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:51.130
Yeah. give us two minutes. shortstop.
I'll put it on your tab.

306
00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:53.040
Thanks. Polaski.

307
00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:56.630
What was that? They knock for you?

308
00:18:56.710 --> 00:18:59.680
Guys. there is one more piece to this
that I think you should know.

309
00:19:00.430 --> 00:19:02.970
Doctors came back
with Jane Doe's medical records.

310
00:19:03.680 --> 00:19:06.220
They found signs of sexual assault.

311
00:19:10.770 --> 00:19:12.730
Denise Hensley was her manager.

312
00:19:13.400 --> 00:19:15.650
Kept her captive. sent money up the chain.

313
00:19:16.400 --> 00:19:17.690
She was being sex trafficked.

314
00:19:17.780 --> 00:19:18.990
Damn it.

315
00:19:19.070 --> 00:19:22.530
Girl managed to get away.
Bosses beat and killed Denise.

316
00:19:25.030 --> 00:19:26.540
I liked it better when it was aliens.

317
00:19:29.910 --> 00:19:32.080
"The room appeared excessively cleaned.

318
00:19:32.170 --> 00:19:35.460
They found no visible fingerprints.
no biological material.

319
00:19:35.540 --> 00:19:37.760
no trace evidence. no random fibers."

320
00:19:37.840 --> 00:19:40.760
That's. uh…
…That's pretty clean for a two-star hotel.

321
00:19:40.840 --> 00:19:42.760
I mean. what do you expect? Roaches?

322
00:19:42.840 --> 00:19:45.010
One negative Yelp review.
corporate will come for my head.

323
00:19:45.100 --> 00:19:47.140
Yeah? What did corporate have to say
about the security cameras

324
00:19:47.220 --> 00:19:48.520
being conveniently nonfunctional?

325
00:19:48.600 --> 00:19:51.350
Yeah. that's been an issue.
We've had a ticket open on that forever.

326
00:19:51.440 --> 00:19:52.940
A ticket!

327
00:19:53.020 --> 00:19:56.270
Tucker. a girl was sex trafficked
in your hotel right under your nose.

328
00:19:56.360 --> 00:19:57.860
and you're telling me
you didn't even notice?

329
00:19:57.940 --> 00:20:00.950
Because it looks to me like you are
a party to human trafficking.

330
00:20:02.150 --> 00:20:03.280
- Wait.
- You're in this.

331
00:20:03.360 --> 00:20:05.370
It's time you start telling us
what you know.

332
00:20:05.450 --> 00:20:07.580
Oh. God. I didn't really think
that they were...

333
00:20:07.660 --> 00:20:09.250
Of course you did!

334
00:20:09.750 --> 00:20:11.540
Did you see the men coming and going?

335
00:20:12.120 --> 00:20:13.830
Did you see the bruises on her body?

336
00:20:14.830 --> 00:20:16.090
What kept you quiet?

337
00:20:18.250 --> 00:20:19.260
Did they pay you off?

338
00:20:19.840 --> 00:20:21.670
Or did you just not want
to make any waves?

339
00:20:22.470 --> 00:20:25.640
It was an envelope of money every week.

340
00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:29.180
- Who rented that room?
- I don't know his name.

341
00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:31.390
Was he the one
who beat Denise Hensley to death?

342
00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:32.690
Oh. I don't know anything about that.

343
00:20:32.770 --> 00:20:36.310
It is against policy to rent a room
to somebody without an ID.

344
00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:38.980
Corporate wanted us to fill
as many rooms as possible. all right?

345
00:20:39.070 --> 00:20:41.900
They-They-They would give us bonuses.
They didn't care about the girls.

346
00:20:41.990 --> 00:20:44.110
Wait. what? Girls?

347
00:20:47.030 --> 00:20:48.120
There were others?

348
00:20:49.990 --> 00:20:53.500
We searched that place
high and low. Tucker.

349
00:20:53.580 --> 00:20:54.750
Where are they?

350
00:20:55.460 --> 00:20:57.170
I don't know.
I don't know. okay?

351
00:20:57.250 --> 00:20:59.500
I really don't know.
I'm sorry. I-I-I don't know.

352
00:21:00.380 --> 00:21:02.340
Well. you can think about it
while you're being processed.

353
00:21:02.420 --> 00:21:04.430
because you are under arrest.

354
00:21:04.510 --> 00:21:05.890
Stand up.

355
00:21:13.230 --> 00:21:14.980
You can go home if you want.
It's getting late.

356
00:21:15.060 --> 00:21:16.600
I'm sure Seth wants to see you.

357
00:21:16.690 --> 00:21:18.900
He will see plenty of me
when this baby comes.

358
00:21:18.980 --> 00:21:20.690
I want to help.

359
00:21:23.150 --> 00:21:25.700
- This one's getting in my bones. Angie.
- I get it.

360
00:21:25.780 --> 00:21:27.530
Trafficking cases will keep you
up at night.

361
00:21:27.620 --> 00:21:32.830
These girls being sold like meat.
Used and discarded like trash.

362
00:21:34.500 --> 00:21:36.370
Some of them are just little kids.

363
00:21:37.250 --> 00:21:38.540
I don't know how they survive it.

364
00:21:38.630 --> 00:21:39.630
A lot of them don't.

365
00:21:42.050 --> 00:21:43.210
Some of us do.

366
00:21:52.640 --> 00:21:55.730
Wait. I… I think. Angie…

367
00:21:55.810 --> 00:21:59.270
I think this is… Is this her? Is this her?

368
00:22:01.070 --> 00:22:02.070
This is her. right?

369
00:22:02.150 --> 00:22:04.440
- Yes. Yes.
- It is. It is. You found her.

370
00:22:04.530 --> 00:22:07.450
Grace Elverton. Her parents reported her
missing last year.

371
00:22:07.530 --> 00:22:10.240
She went to an art festival
and never came home.

372
00:22:11.580 --> 00:22:13.290
Till now.

373
00:22:17.160 --> 00:22:19.830
All right. the background is
Caribbean blue.

374
00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:22.130
Right. the logo should fill the space.

375
00:22:22.210 --> 00:22:24.590
And along the backside. that's
where we have the bar's address.

376
00:22:24.670 --> 00:22:26.130
It's small. yellow. and along the bottom.

377
00:22:26.220 --> 00:22:28.550
It should match the website's font.

378
00:22:28.630 --> 00:22:30.760
You know what?
Let's. uh. crush up the box a little bit.

379
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:33.010
you know. blunt the edges.
make it look a little torn.

380
00:22:33.100 --> 00:22:36.810
and the tracker... this is important...
has to be impossible to notice.

381
00:22:36.890 --> 00:22:39.520
Okay? No added weight. no bulging...

382
00:22:39.600 --> 00:22:41.690
- Yeah.
- Hey. you paying attention?

383
00:22:41.770 --> 00:22:44.230
Yeah. yeah. Yeah. Is your. uh…

384
00:22:44.730 --> 00:22:46.030
Is your dog… …a biter?

385
00:22:49.240 --> 00:22:52.030
- Well. she only bites people who lie.
- No kidding.

386
00:22:52.870 --> 00:22:55.540
Can you deliver this tomorrow
by 4:00 p.m. or not?

387
00:22:55.620 --> 00:22:58.910
- Yeah. man. We're good.
- With a range of one mile.

388
00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:01.670
Yeah. man.

389
00:23:01.750 --> 00:23:03.880
Okay. all right.
Look. more like a thousand feet.

390
00:23:03.960 --> 00:23:07.090
Look. dude. you want invisible
and you want a rush job. all right?

391
00:23:07.170 --> 00:23:09.340
You want better? Go use your guys.

392
00:23:12.850 --> 00:23:13.850
Will?

393
00:23:14.390 --> 00:23:16.520
We gotta go to the back. We gotta go
to the back right now.

394
00:23:16.600 --> 00:23:18.270
Let's go. Come on.

395
00:23:19.230 --> 00:23:20.560
Wait. where's my money?

396
00:23:20.640 --> 00:23:23.520
Okay. look. here's half.
All right. you get the rest on delivery.

397
00:23:23.610 --> 00:23:24.610
What about the deal we made?

398
00:23:24.690 --> 00:23:27.480
Consider it an incentive to be on time.
Now go. Get out of here.

399
00:23:30.820 --> 00:23:31.990
Will.

400
00:23:32.070 --> 00:23:34.740
- Are you in there?
- Coming.

401
00:23:37.290 --> 00:23:40.330
- What are you doing here?
- Checking on you. You gonna let me in?

402
00:23:46.050 --> 00:23:48.760
I had this bad feeling
you weren't really sick.

403
00:23:50.090 --> 00:23:53.260
What? You want a doctor's note?

404
00:23:53.340 --> 00:23:58.020
You have anything?
FBI share any new intel with you?

405
00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:01.940
Not yet.

406
00:24:03.440 --> 00:24:05.860
I'm sorry
Adelaide hasn't called you yet. Will.

407
00:24:08.110 --> 00:24:09.110
Yeah.

408
00:24:09.190 --> 00:24:10.990
Why don't you let the FBI
monitor the phone?

409
00:24:11.070 --> 00:24:12.360
Absolutely not.

410
00:24:12.450 --> 00:24:15.530
It's a good idea.
You shouldn't shoulder this alone.

411
00:24:15.620 --> 00:24:18.950
They'll go after her.
and they'll get him killed.

412
00:24:19.540 --> 00:24:20.790
You know this.

413
00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:29.420
I think about how he must be feeling
right now.

414
00:24:32.550 --> 00:24:33.840
If he's even alive.

415
00:24:35.340 --> 00:24:40.520
- I know how important he is to you.
- It's not just that he's family. Amanda.

416
00:24:42.640 --> 00:24:43.890
He's a bright light.

417
00:24:44.520 --> 00:24:49.480
Will. you'll find him.
You just have to hold on to that light.

418
00:24:51.780 --> 00:24:54.820
You're the most stubborn person I know.
After me.

419
00:24:56.120 --> 00:24:57.120
Hmm.

420
00:24:57.200 --> 00:25:01.330
Never let anyone
make you forget it.

421
00:25:04.540 --> 00:25:06.000
But first…

422
00:25:07.040 --> 00:25:09.000
get healthy.

423
00:25:09.960 --> 00:25:11.760
Call me if you need anything.

424
00:25:15.550 --> 00:25:19.220
And if the phone rings. be careful. Will.

425
00:25:22.180 --> 00:25:23.430
I will.

426
00:25:24.890 --> 00:25:26.150
Okay.

427
00:25:30.770 --> 00:25:33.400
What?

428
00:25:34.570 --> 00:25:38.820
Yes. I know. Don't bite me. okay?

429
00:25:44.620 --> 00:25:46.670
You're here to see that psycho alien girl?

430
00:25:47.170 --> 00:25:49.630
That girl can hear you. asshole.

431
00:25:50.380 --> 00:25:54.470
Never denigrate a victim again.
You're relieved.

432
00:26:04.930 --> 00:26:08.730
I am sorry about that officer.
I'm gonna have them send someone else.

433
00:26:10.230 --> 00:26:12.650
- It's okay.
- No. No. it's not. Grace.

434
00:26:14.610 --> 00:26:19.660
That's your name. isn't it?
Grace Elverton from Minot. North Dakota?

435
00:26:21.410 --> 00:26:26.040
I spoke with your parents. and they are
so relieved that you're alive.

436
00:26:26.120 --> 00:26:28.420
They were worried about you.

437
00:26:30.210 --> 00:26:32.250
I don't want to see them.

438
00:26:32.340 --> 00:26:35.460
Grace. if there is any reason why
they are not safe for you to go back to.

439
00:26:35.550 --> 00:26:36.550
- then you need...
- No.

440
00:26:37.130 --> 00:26:39.260
That's not it.

441
00:26:41.850 --> 00:26:43.810
I don't want them to see me…

442
00:26:45.180 --> 00:26:46.310
like this.

443
00:26:48.520 --> 00:26:50.850
Listen. all they care about
is that you're okay.

444
00:26:53.020 --> 00:26:55.320
They're buying their plane tickets
right now.

445
00:26:57.490 --> 00:26:58.570
Do they know…

446
00:26:59.990 --> 00:27:00.990
what happened?

447
00:27:01.570 --> 00:27:03.280
They know broad strokes.

448
00:27:05.040 --> 00:27:06.910
But your story is yours to tell.

449
00:27:08.710 --> 00:27:11.420
It might take a while until you're ready.
and that's okay.

450
00:27:15.590 --> 00:27:16.590
They weren't…

451
00:27:18.050 --> 00:27:19.050
aliens.

452
00:27:23.100 --> 00:27:25.010
But how could people have done that?

453
00:27:27.350 --> 00:27:28.680
I don't know. Grace.

454
00:27:30.770 --> 00:27:32.520
But it was not your fault.

455
00:27:36.440 --> 00:27:38.150
May I. please?

456
00:27:41.780 --> 00:27:45.330
The other girls.
I'm trying to help them too.

457
00:27:46.200 --> 00:27:49.620
So can you tell me more?
Who was doing this?

458
00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:51.670
There were four of them.

459
00:27:53.330 --> 00:27:55.460
Bad. bad men.

460
00:27:56.630 --> 00:27:59.460
They gave me this.

461
00:28:04.180 --> 00:28:06.560
- What did they look like?
- Three of them were short.

462
00:28:07.930 --> 00:28:09.980
But one was tall.

463
00:28:12.060 --> 00:28:13.150
Really tall.

464
00:28:15.520 --> 00:28:17.150
He was the worst one.

465
00:28:18.320 --> 00:28:19.570
Do you know his name?

466
00:28:20.860 --> 00:28:23.320
- No.
- How did they move you? How often?

467
00:28:23.410 --> 00:28:25.370
Every couple of weeks.

468
00:28:26.240 --> 00:28:29.160
All together in a truck.

469
00:28:29.790 --> 00:28:32.210
Like. a moving truck.

470
00:28:33.170 --> 00:28:34.500
It was awful.

471
00:28:36.460 --> 00:28:39.090
- I was so scared.
- And you were brave.

472
00:28:40.170 --> 00:28:43.630
You escaped. And now you're safe.

473
00:28:46.640 --> 00:28:47.640
Okay?

474
00:28:50.520 --> 00:28:51.520
You're safe.

475
00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:54.350
Okay. Rocky. What do you got?

476
00:28:54.440 --> 00:28:58.650
Well. there's no camera on
the hotel itself. Just the street nearby.

477
00:28:58.730 --> 00:29:00.190
Can we make a list of all the box trucks

478
00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:01.860
that passed by the night
of Denise's death?

479
00:29:01.940 --> 00:29:03.570
It's a busy street.
That's gonna be something

480
00:29:03.650 --> 00:29:05.490
like a thousand vehicles.

481
00:29:05.570 --> 00:29:09.080
We need a better idea of
when they moved the girls. narrow it down.

482
00:29:09.160 --> 00:29:11.200
I could take another run
at the hotel clerk.

483
00:29:11.290 --> 00:29:13.460
Maybe his little taste of lockup
jogged his memory.

484
00:29:13.540 --> 00:29:16.170
Shelly talked about transmitting signals
into space.

485
00:29:16.250 --> 00:29:18.170
but how would she know
if aliens responded?

486
00:29:18.250 --> 00:29:19.670
She said she didn't have
any video cameras.

487
00:29:19.750 --> 00:29:22.760
Yeah. I'm not talking about video.
I'm talking about audio.

488
00:29:22.840 --> 00:29:24.720
Does this look like a microphone to you?

489
00:29:26.390 --> 00:29:28.890
Shelly. you paranoid genius.

490
00:29:29.510 --> 00:29:32.930
Wait. wait. wait. Okay. Listen to this.

491
00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:37.060
That's the box truck.

492
00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:40.360
That's the aliens.

493
00:29:40.440 --> 00:29:41.820
I'm cold.

494
00:29:41.900 --> 00:29:43.530
That's it. What time was that?

495
00:29:43.610 --> 00:29:45.070
Check it against the cameras.

496
00:29:46.450 --> 00:29:48.620
Get me a truck company name
and a license plate.

497
00:29:48.700 --> 00:29:50.950
We're gonna track these bastards down.

498
00:30:03.760 --> 00:30:07.380
So. that's the Commander?
A child?

499
00:30:09.090 --> 00:30:13.430
"Beware of false prophets who come to you
in sheep's clothing.

500
00:30:14.310 --> 00:30:18.020
but inwardly are ravenous wolves."

501
00:30:59.100 --> 00:31:02.270
Ormewood. That man is very tall.

502
00:31:03.770 --> 00:31:06.820
- Yes. he is.
- Go check the plate on the truck.

503
00:31:16.240 --> 00:31:18.460
GBI! Show me your hands!

504
00:31:21.330 --> 00:31:22.420
Get that guy!

505
00:31:24.380 --> 00:31:27.210
I need backup.
I'm 10-80 with a silver Camaro.

506
00:32:16.010 --> 00:32:17.430
Come here!

507
00:32:39.540 --> 00:32:40.540
Stop!

508
00:32:51.630 --> 00:32:54.010
- Hey.
- I got my guy. You?

509
00:32:54.090 --> 00:32:56.510
- Yep.
- Okay. Let's find these girls.

510
00:33:02.230 --> 00:33:04.640
Hey. we have a team arriving
at the last known location

511
00:33:04.730 --> 00:33:07.060
of the truck's GPS system.
The girls might still be there.

512
00:33:07.150 --> 00:33:08.940
The sex traffickers lawyered up.
They aren't talking.

513
00:33:12.070 --> 00:33:15.990
Okay. House is clear.
The girl's been moved again.

514
00:33:16.700 --> 00:33:19.580
God. He must have called his partners
from the car while I was chasing him.

515
00:33:19.660 --> 00:33:22.120
All this work.
and we're still one step behind.

516
00:33:22.200 --> 00:33:25.370
You know what?
You interrupted their whole operation.

517
00:33:25.460 --> 00:33:29.790
You caught two of them. You reunited Grace
with her family. This is good.

518
00:33:31.500 --> 00:33:32.760
That's not enough.

519
00:33:36.300 --> 00:33:41.720
No. I've just been. uh. you know.
mostly horizontal. but. uh…

520
00:33:41.810 --> 00:33:45.850
No. look. you don't need to worry.
I'll be back at work tomorrow.

521
00:33:45.940 --> 00:33:49.110
How are you sick? You're never sick.
You have the constitution of an ox.

522
00:33:49.730 --> 00:33:51.400
Yeah. I'm sorry to disappoint.

523
00:33:51.480 --> 00:33:54.030
- Well. can I pick you up some soup?
- No. Um…

524
00:33:55.110 --> 00:33:59.490
No. don't-don't put yourself at risk.
Uh. keep that baby safe for me.

525
00:33:59.570 --> 00:34:01.410
All right. Get some rest.

526
00:34:01.490 --> 00:34:04.540
Yeah. Um. thanks. Ang.

527
00:34:06.040 --> 00:34:07.290
Appreciate the check-in.

528
00:34:08.420 --> 00:34:09.880
Have a good night. okay?

529
00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:13.380
You too. Good night.

530
00:34:25.020 --> 00:34:26.940
It's gonna be okay. Betty.

531
00:34:30.400 --> 00:34:35.530
I hope so. anyway.
Look. I have to do this. He's my family.

532
00:34:38.240 --> 00:34:40.780
Of course you are too. Come here. girl.

533
00:34:45.620 --> 00:34:49.750
If anything happens to me.
Nico's gonna take care of you. okay?

534
00:34:51.080 --> 00:34:52.960
You'll have everything you need.
all right?

535
00:34:57.840 --> 00:34:58.840
I know.

536
00:35:06.310 --> 00:35:09.190
Yeah. Yeah.

537
00:35:09.270 --> 00:35:11.150
There you go. There you go.

538
00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:15.230
That's my girl.

539
00:35:37.840 --> 00:35:39.050
See you soon. girl.

540
00:36:09.830 --> 00:36:10.870
Hmm.

541
00:36:10.960 --> 00:36:12.580
Don't you look handsome?

542
00:36:14.500 --> 00:36:15.960
I ordered you a martini.

543
00:36:18.550 --> 00:36:20.720
I don't know what's in that drink.

544
00:36:37.900 --> 00:36:38.900
Aren't you gonna sit?

545
00:36:39.480 --> 00:36:42.820
I'd love to. Once I know he's alive.

546
00:36:44.200 --> 00:36:47.240
Right. those ridiculous questions
you had me ask him.

547
00:36:47.330 --> 00:36:50.200
When Antonio and I first met. we…

548
00:36:50.290 --> 00:36:54.460
Ate at a taco truck
like peasants.

549
00:36:54.540 --> 00:36:55.790
The record he gave me?

550
00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:58.880
Nick Lowe. Jesus of Cool.
Now. that's an album.

551
00:36:58.960 --> 00:37:01.210
The name of Antonio's last dog?

552
00:37:01.300 --> 00:37:03.970
Portia. He had her for 14 years.

553
00:37:05.010 --> 00:37:07.550
I told you he's alive. Now sit down.

554
00:37:14.890 --> 00:37:16.100
Don't mind if I do.

555
00:37:39.420 --> 00:37:41.840
What are you doing?
We only caught two of the traffickers.

556
00:37:46.380 --> 00:37:47.430
You finished?

557
00:37:48.640 --> 00:37:53.060
Forensics matched hair and fibers found
on Denise Hensley's body to our suspects.

558
00:37:53.140 --> 00:37:56.440
Your homicide case is closed.
The trafficking case is still open.

559
00:37:58.020 --> 00:37:59.730
I'm taking this upstairs.

560
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:02.150
Hell. yeah. Mitchell.

561
00:38:04.900 --> 00:38:06.200
Fiber?

562
00:38:07.280 --> 00:38:08.490
Fiber.

563
00:38:09.200 --> 00:38:10.490
Hmm.

564
00:38:13.910 --> 00:38:14.910
Mmm.

565
00:38:16.580 --> 00:38:17.920
You have to try the arancini.

566
00:38:19.290 --> 00:38:21.920
Uh-uh. with the sauce. with the sauce.

567
00:38:34.430 --> 00:38:35.890
Ew.

568
00:38:35.980 --> 00:38:38.770
PDA. We're so gross.

569
00:38:55.450 --> 00:38:56.450
Delicious.

570
00:39:03.750 --> 00:39:04.750
Mmm.

571
00:39:06.260 --> 00:39:08.590
So. do you really still have that matchbox
from Rio's?

572
00:39:09.720 --> 00:39:12.350
- Yes. I wasn't lying.
- Hmm.

573
00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:25.940
How are we doing over here?

574
00:39:26.030 --> 00:39:27.820
Satisfied. thank you.

575
00:39:31.320 --> 00:39:33.280
Hmm.

576
00:39:34.450 --> 00:39:36.160
It takes me right back to the island.

577
00:39:41.920 --> 00:39:43.460
Things were so much simpler then.

578
00:39:47.090 --> 00:39:48.090
What do you mean?

579
00:39:49.260 --> 00:39:50.550
Damn it. watch your step.

580
00:39:50.630 --> 00:39:51.800
I'm… I don't know what happened.

581
00:39:51.890 --> 00:39:52.930
What the hell's wrong with you?

582
00:39:53.010 --> 00:39:54.800
Easy. It's just an accident.

583
00:39:54.890 --> 00:39:57.770
- Stay out of this.
- Oh. okay. Let's take it down. all right?

584
00:40:06.820 --> 00:40:07.820
Damn it.

585
00:40:17.870 --> 00:40:20.000
Adelaide. Hey. where'd you go?

586
00:40:20.960 --> 00:40:22.750
What a shame. Will.

587
00:40:22.830 --> 00:40:26.920
When we made these dinner plans. I really
was gonna give you everything you wanted.

588
00:40:27.420 --> 00:40:31.970
Your uncle. your life. me. All of it.

589
00:40:32.760 --> 00:40:35.800
But you had to go and ruin it
by having your boss go looking for me.

590
00:40:37.310 --> 00:40:40.680
What? No. it didn't happen.

591
00:40:40.770 --> 00:40:46.230
I just wanted to see you one last time
before telling you that it's over. Will.

592
00:40:46.980 --> 00:40:48.780
You're never gonna see Antonio again.

593
00:40:48.860 --> 00:40:51.530
Hang-Hang on a second. okay?
No. we had a deal.

594
00:40:51.610 --> 00:40:53.240
And I've left you a little present.

595
00:40:55.780 --> 00:40:56.780
What?

596
00:40:58.280 --> 00:40:59.660
Adelaide. what did you do?

597
00:41:00.160 --> 00:41:02.660
You'll see. It's right around the corner.

598
00:41:03.750 --> 00:41:05.960
You'll never forget me now. Will.

599
00:41:07.630 --> 00:41:09.130
Adelaide. don't hang up.

600
00:41:17.970 --> 00:41:18.970
No.

601
00:41:23.980 --> 00:41:24.980
No.

602
00:41:25.850 --> 00:41:28.730
No. no. no. no. no. no. no. no.

603
00:41:32.690 --> 00:41:34.900
Amanda.

604
00:41:38.030 --> 00:41:40.870
No. Come here.

605
00:41:40.950 --> 00:41:43.200
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

606
00:41:43.960 --> 00:41:45.120
Come on.

607
00:41:52.760 --> 00:41:54.470
Help!

607
00:41:55.305 --> 00:42:55.492
Do you want subtitles for any video?
